    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "1) &quot;<i>Why ?</i>&quot;: because it is explicitly allowed by the Java Language Specification <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-5.html#jls-5.5-130\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">5.5. Casting Contexts</a>: &quot;<i>If the expression has the null type, then the expression may be cast to any reference type.</i>&quot;; 2) &quot;<i>It prints <code>null</code>. But <code>.toString()</code> method should throw a null pointer exception</i>&quot; - no, <code>println(String)</code> (<code>print(String)</code>) is <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/io/PrintStream.html#print(java.lang.String)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">documented</a> to print <code>&quot;null&quot;</code> if its argument is <code>null</code>"
  } ],
  "answers" : [ {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1138392,
