  "title" : "No Exception while type casting with a null in Java",
  "body" : "<p>Consider:</p>\n<pre><code>String x = (String) null;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Why isn’t there any exception in this statement?</p>\n<pre><code>String x = null;\nSystem.out.println(x);\n</code></pre>\n<p>It prints <code>null</code>. But <code>.toString()</code> method should throw a null pointer exception.</p>\n"
